title.rendered: TNPL 2022, SS vs NRK Prediction: Who will win today’s 4th Match?

content.rendered:
Salem Spartans will cross swords with Nellai Royal Kings in the fourth match of the Tamil Nadu Premier League (TNPL) 2022 at the Indian Cement Company Ground in Tirunelveli.
The Salem Spartans’ first match of the season will be this one. The task of leading the team in the TNPL 2022 has been given to Murugan Ashwin. Vijay Shankar and Washington Sundar are two seasoned players who will try to help the club succeed. Everyone was pleased by G Periyaswamy last season, and he is undoubtedly a player to look forward to.

The Salem Spartans had just five points when they finished seventh the previous season. They only succeeded in winning two of their seven games, and they’ll undoubtedly try to improve in this year’s competition.

In contrast, the Nellai Royal Kings started this edition off without a hitch. In order to start their campaign on a winning note, they took on the reigning champions Chepauk Super Gillies, whom they overcame in a thrilling match.

The Royal Kings scored 184 runs after being asked to bat first, but they lost four wickets in the process. The Super Gillies forced the game to a Super Over despite the bowlers’ best efforts. The Royal Kings successfully chased it down with one ball remaining thanks to superb bowling from V Athisayaraj Davidson, who only let up nine runs.

Will Salem Spartans (SS) beat Nellai Royal Kings (NRK)?

The Salem Spartans had a difficult season last year. This season, they have a good deal of experience among their ranks, and they intend to begin the competition strongly. The Spartans have some interesting athletes on their team, and if they perform to the best of their abilities, they have a chance to win it all.

The Nellai Royal Kings, on the other hand, will be full of confidence after playing outstandingly against the Chepauk Super Gillies in their TNPL 2022 season opener. The Royal Kings are likely to keep up their winning streak because of their strong side’s balance.

Prediction: Salem Spartans to win this clash
